#: ../../tutorials/05_problem_transformers.ipynb:334
msgid "The ``FreezeCoreTransformer``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../tutorials/05_problem_transformers.ipynb:336
msgid ""
"This transformer provides you with the very simple means to freeze the "
"*core orbitals* of your molecular system. It requires your problem to "
"contain the ``.molecule`` attribute from which it can extract the atomic "
"information necessary to perform this Hilbert space reduction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../tutorials/05_problem_transformers.ipynb:421
msgid ""
"In the following, we apply the ``FreezeCoreTransformer`` which in this "
"case will remove the single lowest energy orbital (reducing the total "
"number of spatial orbitals from 6 to 5) and also removing the two "
"electrons from within that orbital (as reflected by the changed number of"
" particles)."
msgstr ""

