#: ../../tutorials/05_problem_transformers.ipynb:584
msgid "The ``ActiveSpaceTransformer``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../tutorials/05_problem_transformers.ipynb:586
msgid ""
"This transformer generalizes the Hilbert space reduction which is "
"performed by the ``FreezeCoreTransformer``. Simply put, it allows you to "
"specify an *active space* by selecting the number of active electrons and"
" the number of active spatial orbitals. According to these settings, the "
"active space will be chosen around the Fermi level."
msgstr ""

#: ../../tutorials/05_problem_transformers.ipynb:735
msgid ""
"The ``ActiveSpaceTransformer`` in Qiskit Nature has one more trick up its"
" sleeve because it even allows you to manually specify the indices of the"
" active orbitals. This enables you to hand-pick active spaces which do "
"not lie continuously around the Fermi level."
msgstr ""

